entry.content:
When triggered on a CL, this builder will handle testing that CL on all

builders defined to be on Chromium's "Mega CQ". (Namely, that's trybot

will be deleted outright.) For now, we'll simply use the normal

trybot triggering-flow (`git cl try` or "CHOOSE TRYJOBS" button) to

launch it.

entry.title: [omnibox] Don't transfer sync old matches.
entry.content:
Autocompletion has a step where it transfers the matches from the

previous results to avoid async suggestions disappearing during sync

passes. This is pretty finicky, but necessary.



Currently, transferring skips:

a) matches from providers that already done.

b) actions which are recomputed for each pass.



It's safe to skip those because if they're still releveant to the new

input, they would have already been included in the new matches.



It's useful to skip those to avoid stale matches; e.g. 'github.com' when

the user's typed 'google.com'.



This CL adds' a 3rd case to skip:

c) match types that are always guaranteed to be sync; i.e.

search|url-what-you-typed matches.



These are safe to skip for the same reason; they'll be in the new

matches anyways.



These are useful to skip for the same reason, to avoid stale matches.

But that's relevant even more so in this case, since what-you-typed

suggestions are guaranteed to be stale when inputs change.

entry.title: aura: implement DesktopNativeWidgetAura reparenting
entry.content:
DNWA can have another DNWA as parent on initialization. However,

reparenting a DNWA using Widget::ReparentNativeView() causes many

issues, including but not exclusive to:

- the child content aura::Window will be freed twice on destruction.

- the child content aura::Window is parented to the content aura::Window

of parent DNWA. This results in the content window detached to its

owning accelerated window. The child content aura::Window should

instead remain to be the child of WindowTreeHost's aura::Window.



This CL plumbs reparenting into WindowTreeHost and fixes both issues.

On Windows, the HWND child / owned relationship is updated for

reparenting. Other platforms' accelerated widget will be updated in

follow-up CLs.

entry.title: NavigationActivation prototype
entry.content:
NavigationActivation is a new object (exposed as

`navigation.activation`). It is updated when a new Document is

"activated": initial Document creation, restore from bfcache, or

(in a future CL) prerender activation. It has three pieces of state:

* `activation.entry`: The current NavigationHistoryEntry at the time

of activation.

* `activation.from`: The current NavigationHistoryEntry immediately

before activation (i.e., the entry we came from). This will be

null if the navigation was cross-origin, or if the previous entry

was not in the same-origin contiguous region of the back/forward

list that is available in `navigation.entries()`.

* `activation.navigationType`: The navigationType ('push', 'replace',

'reload', or 'traverse') of the navigation that activated the

current Document.



Note that `entry` or `from` may be a NavigationHistoryEntry that is

no longer present in `navigation.entries()` (e.g., when doing a

replace navigation, `activation.from` will be the replaced entry).

In that case, the entry will remain visible, but because it is

a "disposed" entry, its index will be -1 and attempting to

`navigation.traverseTo()` its key will be rejected.



Initial discussion: https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/9760

Draft spec PR: https://github.com/whatwg/html/pull/9856

entry.title: [Signin] Prevent SigninManager from signout if token is valid
entry.content:
Currently the `SigninManager` will signout all accounts if accounts on

the web are empty and sync feature is off. This makes the

`SigninManager` compete with the reconcilor.



This CL prevents the `SigninManager` from doing a complete signout if

accounts on the web are empty but the primary account refresh token is

empty. This allows the reconcilor to rebuild the session.



Note: User intentionally deleting `GaiaConstants::kGaiaSigninCookieName`

will lead to the reconcilor revoking tokens and as a result the

`SigninManager` will clear the primary account. Other cookie deletion

(e.g. HFCR cookie) will trigger the reconcilor to rebuild cookies.

entry.title: Move OnMemoryPressure to a worker thread.
entry.content:

thread. It could take a significant time to acquire `lock_` when the

browser process to be killed and uses lose their states. This CL

moves OnMemoryPressure to a worker thread so that UI thread is not

held up.

entry.content:

V8 was only used as a fallback for very large Wasm functions, due to

some pathological compile times with the top-tier regalloc.

Since we have fixed the (known) issues in the top-tier register

- the gin feature,

entry.title: Deduplicate Bloom filter hashes.

Add a very simple deduplicator, reducing the need to save the same

hashes over and over again. This is nowhere near perfect (and it is

incompatible with the idea of reordering hashes so that they come

in cache-friendly order), but it saves yet more RAM, and interestingly,

gains back what we lost in the Sports test.
